#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.233"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.233:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.233:0.2"
msgid "24. Kammavagga "
msgstr "24. Deeds "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.233:0.3"
msgid "233. Vitthārasutta "
msgstr "233. Deeds in Detail "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.231, sc1
msgctxt "an4.233:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with my own insight. "

msgctxt "an4.233:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol><li>
msgctxt "an4.233:1.3"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ; "
msgstr "There are dark deeds with dark results; "

#. HTML: </li><li>
msgctxt "an4.233:1.4"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ; "
msgstr "bright deeds with bright results; "

#. HTML: </li><li>
msgctxt "an4.233:1.5"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ; "
msgstr "dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results; and "

#. HTML: </li><li>
msgctxt "an4.233:1.6"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds. "

#. HTML: </li></ol><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.233:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ? "
msgstr "And what are dark deeds with dark results? "

#. VAR: sabyābajjhaṃ → sabyāpajjhaṃ (sabbattha)
msgctxt "an4.233:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti. "
msgstr "It’s when someone makes hurtful choices by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an4.233:2.3"
msgid "So sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā sabyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "Having made these choices, they’re reborn in a hurtful world, "

msgctxt "an4.233:2.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sabyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ sabyābajjhā phassā phusanti. "
msgstr "where hurtful contacts touch them. "

#. VAR: vediyati → vedayati (mr)
msgctxt "an4.233:2.5"
msgid "So sabyābajjhehi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno sabyābajjhaṃ vedanaṃ vediyati ekantadukkhaṃ, seyyathāpi sattā nerayikā. "
msgstr "Touched by hurtful contacts, they experience hurtful feelings that are exclusively painful—like the beings in hell. "

msgctxt "an4.233:2.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ. "
msgstr "These are called dark deeds with dark results. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.233:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ? "
msgstr "And what are bright deeds with bright results? "

msgctxt "an4.233:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, abyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, abyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti. "
msgstr "It’s when someone makes pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an4.233:3.3"
msgid "So abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, abyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, abyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā abyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "Having made these choices, they’re reborn in a pleasing world, "

msgctxt "an4.233:3.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ abyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ abyābajjhā phassā phusanti. "
msgstr "where pleasing contacts touch them. "

msgctxt "an4.233:3.5"
msgid "So abyābajjhehi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno abyābajjhaṃ vedanaṃ vediyati ekantasukhaṃ, seyyathāpi devā subhakiṇhā. "
msgstr "Touched by pleasing contacts, they experience pleasing feelings that are exclusively happy—like the gods replete with glory. "

msgctxt "an4.233:3.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ. "
msgstr "These are called bright deeds with bright results. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.232, sc4
msgctxt "an4.233:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ? "
msgstr "And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results? "

msgctxt "an4.233:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti. "
msgstr "It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an4.233:4.3"
msgid "So sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi lokaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "Having made these choices, they are reborn in a world that is both hurtful and pleasing, "

msgctxt "an4.233:4.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ sabyābajjhāpi abyābajjhāpi phassā phusanti. "
msgstr "where hurtful and pleasing contacts touch them. "

msgctxt "an4.233:4.5"
msgid "So sabyābajjhehipi abyābajjhehipi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vedanaṃ vediyati vokiṇṇasukhadukkhaṃ, seyyathāpi manussā ekacce ca devā ekacce ca vinipātikā. "
msgstr "Touched by both hurtful and pleasing contacts, they experience both hurtful and pleasing feelings that are a mixture of pleasure and pain—like humans, some gods, and some beings in the underworld. "

msgctxt "an4.233:4.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ. "
msgstr "These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.233:5.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati? "
msgstr "And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds? "

#. VAR: yamidaṃ → yampidaṃ (bj, pts1) | yampīdaṃ (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: yamidaṃ → yampidaṃ (bj, pts1) | yampīdaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.233:5.2"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā, yamidaṃ kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā—"
msgstr "It’s the intention to give up dark deeds with dark results, bright deeds with bright results, and both dark and bright deeds with both dark and bright results. "

msgctxt "an4.233:5.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.233:5.4"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.233:5.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

